  PART IV: THE THREE-LAYER ARCHITECTURE

  - 4.1 The Bedrock Layer
    - Hardware and kernel — cannot be overridden by userspace
    - TrustZone root of trust: ed25519 keys in hardware-isolated execution environment
    - dm-verity: cryptographic block-level integrity checking of system partitions (runs even in orange state)
    - Telux-SEC: LSM kernel module enforcing Island boundaries at kernel level
    - Hardware power domain controller: peripheral power gating as physical fact
    - "These are physical facts, not policy"
  - 4.2 The Submerged Layer
    - Where ZAKO's intelligence lives
    - Outstack: power governor, process class enforcement, execution gating, five-mode state machine
    - Telux daemons: telux-ledgerd (append-only ledger), telux-identd (key custodian, signing, capability grants), telux-sharedb (outbound transmission mediation)
    - Identity service: DID ecosystem for every entity (human, machine, AI, service)
    - Reads from Bedrock, expresses policy upward
  - 4.3 The Visible Layer
    - The surface: group interfaces, exchange queries, telephony, applications, natural language query
    - Built on AOSP — not because Android is perfect but because it is proven
    - Runs on existing hardware, mature build infrastructure, auditable without commercial dependency
    - No Google Mobile Services

