  PART VII: TELUX — THE EXCHANGE LAYER

  - 7.1 The Sovereign Network Model
    - A single device is a complete network
    - Islands, daemons, sub-entities exchanging signed records
    - Fractal: same protocol at every scale (record → sub-entity → device → device-to-device → newgroup → distribution)
  - 7.2 The Daemon Triad
    - telux-ledgerd (CRITICAL): Append-only ledger, sole source of truth, conservation enforcement, fsync before ACK — always
    - telux-identd (CRITICAL): Key custodian, DID manager, capability grants, identity lock (refuses signing when screen locked)
    - telux-sharedb (INTERACTIVE): Outbound transmission, channel selection (SMS, QR, BLE, IP), per-channel formatting
  - 7.3 Islands and Sovereignty
    - Six axioms: Primacy, Origin, Creation right, Life/death, Non-interference, Power flows down
    - Sovereignty declaration: Island ID, Sovereign DID, type, succession rules, constraints, witnesses
    - Constraint types: MaxGroups, MaxMembers, MaxPower, TimeLimit, GeographicBound, RequireWitness, ProhibitAction, RequireAudit, CannotDelegate
    - Enforcement tiers: VISIBLE (policy), SUBMERGED (cgroups), BEDROCK (LSM hooks)
  - 7.4 The newgroup Primitive
    - Evolution of Linux group: humans, services, APIs, AI models, IoT devices
    - Dynamic, permanent or temporary
    - Every member identified by W3C DID
    - Non-human entities get first-class membership with capabilities, power budgets, auditable records
  - 7.5 Identity
    - ed25519 keys backed by Keymaster 4.0 (TrustZone)
    - W3C DIDs (did:key method, z6Mk prefix)
    - Chain hash: BLAKE3(frame_hash[n] || chain_hash[n-1])
    - Genesis anchor: BLAKE3(frame_hash[0] || zeros_32)
    - Island ID: BASE58URL(BLAKE3(public_key || epoch))
    - Capability grants as signed delegation, depth-limited (max 3 levels), revocable with cascade
  - 7.6 The Exchange Ledger
    - Every transfer between Island members is a ledger entry
    - Created before operation completes, signed, hashed, chained to predecessors
    - Cannot be deleted, queryable by authorized parties
    - Natural language query interface: rule-based FSM for "what did X send to Y", time parsing
    - Transmission via SMS (pads-v1 URL format <300 chars), QR code, BLE, IP

