  PART IX: THE CODEBOOK AND PICTOGRAPHY

  - 9.1 The Codebook Standard
    - 64 task code verbs across all domains
    - Domain declarations: Financial (0x00–0x0F), Work (0x10–0x1F), Health (0x20–0x2F), Academy (0x30–0x3F), Location (0x40–0x4F), Social (0x50–0x5F), Agreements (0x60–0x6F),
  Schedule (0x70–0x7F)
    - Quantity types: monetary, energy, mass, data, time, service
    - Account pair relationships: Source/Sink, Asset/Liability, Equity/Reserve, Revenue/Expense
  - 9.2 Binary Pictography
    - 4 bits per symbol, 16 symbols per domain codebook
    - Core codebook (Category 0x0F): 16 ZAKO-wide symbols (OK, FAIL, WAIT, SEND, RECEIVE, LOCK, UNLOCK, POWER, ALERT, etc.)
    - 8 domain-specific codebooks (Exchange, Work, Health, Academy, Location, Social, Agreements, Schedule)
    - Maximum 8 symbols (4 bytes) without intervening structural record
    - Four-symbol convention: event, cause/context, sub-entity/domain, status/outcome
    - Context Declaration Wave (4 bytes) switches active codebook
    - Pure Signal + symbol byte: 2-byte minimum state signal (e.g., CONSERVE+ACK)
    - ALERT (0xF) from any codebook always promoted to INTERACTIVE — dropping ALERT is protocol violation

